{
  "text": "By equating the right-hand sides of Eqs. ͑7͒ and ͑8͒, Porté-Agel et al. [CITATION_1] obtained a fifth-order polynomial in ␤, including ten terms ͑tensor contractions involving various filtered strain-rates and resolved stress tensors͒ that need to be averaged over directions of statistical homogeneity. [CITATION_2] The polynomial is solved for ␤ and the solution is then replaced in Eq. ͑7͒ to obtain a scale-dependent estimate of c s,⌬ . This implementation of the scale-dependent model, used in Porté-Agel et al., [CITATION_3] worked well with the planar averaging approach.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "15845952",
